FACEBOX

Facebox

Facebox provides facial detection and recognition in images.

CheckFaceprint Method #↑

CheckFaceprint checks to see if a Faceprint matches any known faces.

CheckFaceprintRequest

  • faceprints Array of string —Faceprints is a list of Faceprints to check.

CheckFaceprintResponse

  • faces Array of FaceprintFace —Faces is a list of faces checked from Faceprints.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

CheckFile Method #↑

CheckFile checks an image file for faces.

CheckFileRequest

  • file remototypes.File —File is the image to check for faces.

CheckFileResponse

  • faces Array of Face —Faces is a list of faces that were found.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

CheckURL Method #↑

CheckURL checks a hosted image file for faces.

CheckURLRequest

  • url string —URL is the address of the image to check.

CheckURLResponse

  • faces Array of Face —Faces is a list of faces that were found.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

FaceprintCompare Method #↑

FaceprintCompare compares faceprints to a specified target describing similarity.

FaceprintCompareRequest

  • target string —Target is the target Faceprint to which the Faceprints will be compared.
  • faceprints Array of string —Faceprints is a list of Faceprints that will be compared to Target.

FaceprintCompareResponse

  • confidences Array of float64 —Confidences is a list of confidence values. The order matches the order of FaceprintCompareRequest.Faceprints.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

GetState Method #↑

GetState gets the Facebox state file.

GetStateRequest

  • No fields —An empty object.

remototypes.FileResponse

  • File

PutState Method #↑

PutState sets the Facebox state file.

PutStateRequest

  • state_file remototypes.File —StateFile is the Facebox state file to set.

PutStateResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

RemoveID Method #↑

RemoveID removes a face with the specified ID.

RemoveIDRequest

  • id string —ID is the identifier of the source to remove.

RemoveIDResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

Rename Method #↑

Rename changes a person's name.

RenameRequest

  • from string —From is the original name.
  • to string —To is the new name.

RenameResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

RenameID Method #↑

RenameID changes the name of a previously taught face, by ID.

RenameIDRequest

  • id string —ID is the identifier of the source to rename.
  • name string —Name is the new name to assign to the item matching ID.

RenameIDResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

SimilarFile Method #↑

SimilarFile checks for similar faces from the face in an image file.

SimilarFileRequest

  • file remototypes.File

SimilarFileResponse

  • faces Array of SimilarFace
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

SimilarID Method #↑

SimilarID checks for similar faces by ID.

SimilarIDRequest

  • id string —ID is the identifier of the source to look for similar faces of.

SimilarIDResponse

  • faces Array of SimilarFace —Faces is a list of similar faces.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

SimilarURL Method #↑

SimilarURL checks for similar faces in a hosted image file.

SimilarURLRequest

  • url string

SimilarURLResponse

  • faces Array of SimilarFace
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

TeachFaceprint Method #↑

TeachFaceprint teaches Facebox about a face from a Faceprint.

TeachFaceprintRequest

  • id string
  • name string
  • faceprint string

TeachFaceprintResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

TeachFile Method #↑

TeachFile teaches Facebox a new face from an image file.

TeachFileRequest

  • id string —ID is an identifier describing the source, for example the filename.
  • name string —Name is the name of the person in the image.
  • file remototypes.File —File is the image containing the face to teach.

TeachFileResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

TeachURL Method #↑

TeachURL teaches Facebox a new face from an image on the web.

TeachURLRequest

  • id string —ID is an identifier describing the source, for example the filename.
  • name string —Name is the name of the person in the image.
  • url string —URL is the address of the image.

TeachURLResponse

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

CheckFaceprintRequest Object #↑

CheckFaceprintRequest is the request object for CheckFaceprint calls.

  • faceprints Array of string —Faceprints is a list of Faceprints to check.

CheckFaceprintResponse Object #↑

CheckFaceprintResponse is the response object for CheckFaceprint calls.

  • faces Array of FaceprintFace —Faces is a list of faces checked from Faceprints.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

CheckFileRequest Object #↑

CheckFileRequest is the request object for CheckFile calls.

  • file remototypes.File —File is the image to check for faces.

CheckFileResponse Object #↑

CheckFileResponse is the response object for CheckFile calls.

  • faces Array of Face —Faces is a list of faces that were found.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

CheckURLRequest Object #↑

CheckURLRequest is the request object for CheckURL calls.

  • url string —URL is the address of the image to check.

CheckURLResponse Object #↑

CheckURLResponse is the response object for CheckURL calls.

  • faces Array of Face —Faces is a list of faces that were found.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

Face Object #↑

Face describes a face.

  • id string —ID is the identifier of the source that was matched.
  • name string —Name is the name of the identified person.
  • matched bool —Matched is whether the face was recognized or not.
  • faceprint string —Faceprint is the Facebox Faceprint of this face.
  • rect Rect —Rect is where the face appears in the source image.

FaceprintCompareRequest Object #↑

FaceprintCompareRequest is the request object for FaceprintCompare calls.

  • target string —Target is the target Faceprint to which the Faceprints will be compared.
  • faceprints Array of string —Faceprints is a list of Faceprints that will be compared to Target.

FaceprintCompareResponse Object #↑

FaceprintCompareResponse is the response object for FaceprintCompare calls.

  • confidences Array of float64 —Confidences is a list of confidence values. The order matches the order of FaceprintCompareRequest.Faceprints.
  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

FaceprintFace Object #↑

FaceprintFace is a face.

  • matched bool —Matched is whether the face was recognized or not.
  • confidence float64 —Confidence is a numerical value of how confident the AI is that this is a match.
  • id string —ID is the identifier of the source that matched.
  • name string —Name is the name of the person recognized.

GetStateRequest Object #↑

GetStateRequest is the request object for GetState calls.

  • No fields —An empty object.

PutStateRequest Object #↑

PutStateRequest is the request object for PutState calls.

  • state_file remototypes.File —StateFile is the Facebox state file to set.

PutStateResponse Object #↑

PutStateResponse is the response object for PutState calls.

  • error string —Error is an error message if one occurred.

Rect Object #↑

Rect is a bounding box describing a rectangle of an image.

  • top int —Top is the starting Y coordinate.
  • left int —Left is the starting X coordinate.
  • width int —Width is the width.
  • height int —Height is the height.

RemoveIDResponse Object #↑

RemoveIDResponse is the response object for RemoveID calls.

SimilarFace Object #↑

Special types

This section describes specially handled types for situations more complex than simple key/value.

remototypes.FileResponse Object #↑

remototypes.FileResponse is used by methods that return a single file as its result.

Client libraries will provide a way to access the returned file.

remototypes.File Object #↑

remototypes.File represents a binary file. Client libraries will each have their own special way of submitting the files.
